---
import Section from "@/components/ui/Section.astro";
import SectionHeader from "@/components/ui/SectionHeader.astro";
---

<Section bg="white" width="md">
  <div class="text-center">
    <SectionHeader subtitle="The problem" subtitleColor="brown" />
    <h2 class="mb-8 font-display text-3xl tracking-tight md:text-4xl">
      Your code works.<br /><em class="text-brown">Your AI can't work with&nbsp;it.</em>
    </h2>
    <p class="mb-6 text-lg leading-relaxed text-ink-muted">
      Brownfield codebases have a unique challenge: the bad patterns have been there so long they look normal. Implicit conventions, undocumented side effects, tightly-coupled modules — humans navigate these over years. AI sees&nbsp;chaos.
    </p>
    <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-ink-muted">
      You can't just drop AI into a legacy codebase and expect it to ship features. It needs <strong class="text-ink">explicit conventions</strong>, <strong class="text-ink">documented architecture</strong>, and <strong class="text-ink">the right skills for each&nbsp;task</strong>.
    </p>
  </div>
</Section>
